      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:4:84:7",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " نَهَانِي أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) أَنْ أَتَكَلَّمَ بَيْنَ الْأَرْبَعِ رَكَعَاتٍ الَّتِي بَعْدَ الْمَغْرِبِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Salma Bin Al Khattab, from Al Husayn Bin Sayf, from Muhammad Bin Yaya, from Hajjaj Al Khashhab, from Abu Al Fawaris who said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> forbade us to speak in between the four <span class=\"iTxt\">Rak’at</span> of <span class=\"iTxt\">Salāt</span> which are after <span class=\"iTxt\">Al-Maghrib</span>’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "7. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Salmah ibn al-Khattab from al-Husayn ibn Sayf from Muhammad ibn Yahya from Hajjaj al- Khashshab from abu al-Fawaris who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, prohibited me from speaking between the four Rak‘at after al- Maghrib.” "
        ]
      }
